23/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The Greek government plans to unveil its massive security plan for the Summer Olympics at an international conference on Monday (24 May), Public Order Minister Yiorgos Voulgarakis announced. During the three-day meeting, security service and police chiefs from the 25 EU member states, the United States, Israel and Australia will be joined by security officials from 202 national Olympic committees. The visiting officials will be able to inspect security arrangements at three locations -- the main stadium, the Olympic village and the site of the archery event. (AP, AFP - 22/05/04)
